notesStmt.note: This pocket-size Book of Hours was created ca. 1380 to commemorate the wedding of Raoul II de Raineval (d. 1392) and Isabelle de Coucy (d. 1413). Its most unique feature is the illuminated heraldic initials containing the arms of Coucy and Raineval at canonical divisions. Particularly, the combined heraldry at Matins in the Hours of the Virgin highlights their marriage. The bride is depicted in a donor portrait kneeling in front of the seated Virgin and Child in one of the prefatory miniatures (fol. 3v) with Coucy's heraldic shield. Charming drolleries appear at major text divisions.

msContents.textLang: The primary language in this manuscript is French, Old (842-ca.1400). The secondary language of this manuscript is Latin.

msItem.title: Book of Hours
msItem.note: Use of Paris; written in French with Latin rubrics

msItem.title: Prefatory image cycle
msItem.note: No text; image cycle with female saints and donor

msItem.title: Hours of the Virgin
msItem.note: Use of Paris; main text in French with Latin opening invocation; fol. 23r: instruction for French and Latin recitations of "Pater noster" underlined in red before Lesson 1 in Matins; fols. 118r-v: prayer for female suppliants after "Magnificat" in Vespers

msItem.title: Seven Penitential Psalms
msItem.rubric: Septem psalmi. Domine ne in furore tuo
msItem.note: Latin incipits used as rubrics, followed by the main text in French; blank fols. 160v-161v

support.p: Medium to heavy parchment, well prepared; flyleaves are modern parchment

supportDesc.foliation: Modern pencil foliation, upper right corners rectos

p.formula: Quire 1: 4, first folio missing (fols. 1-3); Quires 2-10: 8 (fols. 4-75); Quire 11: 6 (fols. 76-81); Quire 12: 8 (fols. 82-89); Quire 13: 4 (fols. 90-93); Quires 14-21: 8 (fols. 94-157); Quire 22: 4 (fols. 158-161)
p.signatures: Several signatures extant, lower right corners rectos, eg. fol. 76r
p.catchwords: Centered on versos lower margin throughout

decoDesc.decoNote: Three full-page miniatures; eight heraldic initials in Hours of the Virgin (4-5 lines); one heraldic initial at the beginning of Penitential Psalms (4 lines); decorated initials at secondary text divisions (2 lines); gold versals on cusped rose and blue ground with white patterns flourish throughout (1 line); vine boarders around main text divisions, drolleries at bas-de-page, occasionally accompanied by winged dragons; line fillers with geometric motifs throughout; rubrics in red throughout; text in medium brown ink

binding.p: Rebound by Léon Gruel, Paris, late nineteenth or early twentieth century; red leather over possibly original wooden boards; possibly original sewing, sewn on five tawed (?) thongs; clasps are modern; fore-edge tabs contemporary with rebinding

origin.origDate: Last quarter of the 14th century CE

history.provenance: Created ca. 1380 in Paris for the marriage of Raoul II de Raineval (d. 1392) and Isabelle de Coucy (d. 1413)

Léon Gruel, Paris, late nineteenth or early twentieth century; his bookplate on front pastedown, unnumbered; number '1476' found on his handwritten dealer description originally attached to front flyleaf, now in WAM file (slip has been imaged here with manuscript)
Henry Walters, Baltimore, purchased from Gruel before 1931
history.acquisition: Walters Art Museum, 1931, by Henry Walters' bequest
